1
00:02:13,065 --> 00:02:14,896
[Man] All right, people.
This is Agent Ford.

2
00:02:14,967 --> 00:02:19,666
We're almost there.
Let's make it count.

3
00:02:19,738 --> 00:02:22,400
This is a surveillance op.
We do not want this guy.

4
00:02:22,474 --> 00:02:25,841
I repeat. Do not let him
I.D. You. He's just the driver.

5
00:02:25,911 --> 00:02:28,311
Eagle One.
Gimme a heads-up.

6
00:02:28,380 --> 00:02:31,110
Eagle One has
target in sight.

7
00:02:31,183 --> 00:02:33,674
Target moving east
on Third. Over.

8
00:02:33,752 --> 00:02:35,686
Roger, Eagle One.

9
00:02:37,957 --> 00:02:41,893
C.P. Is following.
Packages are right there in back.

10
00:03:09,888 --> 00:03:12,789
[Ford] Eagle One, you copy
the black Mustang?

11
00:03:14,526 --> 00:03:17,927
[Eagle One] Roger, C.P.
There's a second one closing in also.

12
00:03:23,268 --> 00:03:24,895
Shit!

13
00:03:29,241 --> 00:03:31,300
[Ford]
He's made us. Maintain pursuit.

14
00:03:31,377 --> 00:03:33,811
Repeat. Maintain pursuit.

15
00:03:36,415 --> 00:03:39,509
Get the plates
on those Mustangs!

16
00:03:43,889 --> 00:03:46,483
Do not lose that driver.
He's our only link to the buyers.

17
00:03:56,068 --> 00:03:58,935
[Horn Blaring]

18
00:04:44,383 --> 00:04:46,476
[Gasps]

19
00:04:52,224 --> 00:04:56,524
- F.B.I.! Freeze! Freeze!
- Don't shoot! A.T.F.!

20
00:04:56,595 --> 00:05:00,531
- Agent McClaren, A.T.F.
- What the hell's A.T.F. Doin'
on an F.B.I. Operation?

21
00:05:00,599 --> 00:05:03,727
- And you are?
- Allen Ford.

22
00:05:03,802 --> 00:05:08,501
I'm sensing a lot of hostility here.
There's no reason to get defensive.

23
00:05:08,574 --> 00:05:12,476
You've got yourself a dead driver
and a cute little shipment of guns!

24
00:05:12,544 --> 00:05:15,536
But ya don't have the seller,
and ya don't have the buyer!

25
00:05:15,614 --> 00:05:18,174
All you've done is shown
the man we're on to him.

26
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:20,741
A.T.F. What does that
stand for, anyway?

27
00:05:20,819 --> 00:05:25,153
Alcohol, Tobacco
and Fuckups?

28
00:05:25,224 --> 00:05:27,818
Definitely a lot of hostility.

29
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:32,795
[Foghorn Wailing]

30
00:05:32,865 --> 00:05:37,359
[Ship Horn Blaring]

31
00:05:43,642 --> 00:05:45,576
[Man]
Change your nozzle!

32
00:05:54,186 --> 00:05:57,917
Hey, Tommy, you're takin' a little
longer than you should with that!

33
00:05:57,990 --> 00:06:00,390
Let's go! Let's go!

34
00:06:03,595 --> 00:06:06,086
Come on. Come on!

35
00:06:06,165 --> 00:06:08,395
- Come on! Let's go!
- Find out what that problem was?

36
00:06:08,467 --> 00:06:11,459
Supposed to be 3/16ths!

37
00:06:11,537 --> 00:06:16,873
Jeff, do I have to remind you
what happened last week?

38
00:06:16,942 --> 00:06:20,241
Come on, Billy.
Get a mop and clean that up.

39
00:06:21,780 --> 00:06:23,805
- Crews!
- Yeah.

40
00:06:23,882 --> 00:06:25,816
I need this one today.

41
00:06:25,884 --> 00:06:28,614
[Man]
Manuel, main-end rod bearing!

42
00:06:28,687 --> 00:06:32,350
- Mr. Cutler said tomorrow.
- I don't give a shit
what Mr. Cutler said.

43
00:06:32,424 --> 00:06:35,587
I got a bunch of loads going out.
I need this one today.

44
00:06:37,796 --> 00:06:40,492
- [Mutters]
- Is that a problem?

45
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:46,061
Uh, no, sir... Just I told my wife I'd
pick my daughter up from school and...

46
00:06:46,138 --> 00:06:48,834
Well, that's real fatherly of you,
but if you want to keep this job,

47
00:06:48,907 --> 00:06:51,637
you're gonna stay here
till it's finished.

48
00:06:51,710 --> 00:06:55,373
- Hey, Greg, can you give me
a hand over here?
- If you need it, it'll be done.

49
00:07:01,353 --> 00:07:04,686
- Mr. Cutler wanted to see me?
- He's expecting you, Jack.

50
00:07:04,756 --> 00:07:07,384
- [Knocking]
- Come in!

51
00:07:07,459 --> 00:07:11,862
[Phone Ringing]

52
00:07:14,633 --> 00:07:18,501
- Yes, sir. You wanted to see me?
- Sit down, Crews.

53
00:07:26,278 --> 00:07:29,270
- You've been with me, what, Crews,
three weeks now?
- Yes, sir.

54
00:07:29,348 --> 00:07:31,714
Says here, you used
to drive a truck.

55
00:07:31,783 --> 00:07:35,310
I think, uh, "used to drive"
is the operative phrase.

56
00:07:35,387 --> 00:07:37,321
Come on, Jack. Don't be so modest. Your
parole officer says you could drive...

57
00:07:37,389 --> 00:07:40,051
an ice truck through hell
on the 4th of July.

58
00:07:40,125 --> 00:07:42,389
Bet you miss that life,
don't you?

59
00:07:42,461 --> 00:07:46,921
- Being your own boss and
nobody tellin' you what to do.
- Sometimes, I guess.

60
00:07:46,999 --> 00:07:48,967
I bet you miss the money
all the time.

61
00:07:50,802 --> 00:07:54,431
How'd you like a chance
to earn some extra cash?

62
00:07:54,506 --> 00:07:57,475
I got a load I need
brought up from Atlanta.

63
00:07:57,542 --> 00:08:01,501
- Off the books, you know what I mean?
- Sir, if you know I can drive,

64
00:08:01,580 --> 00:08:05,516
you also know that I lost my license
permanently when I went to prison.

65
00:08:05,584 --> 00:08:08,985
The way I see it, you only need
a license if you get pulled over.

66
00:08:09,054 --> 00:08:11,682
You made that Georgia run before,
right? You know how easy it is.

67
00:08:11,757 --> 00:08:14,419
It's 15 hours. Nobody even
has to know you're out of town.

68
00:08:14,493 --> 00:08:17,053
Not even your parole officer. Nobody.

69
00:08:17,129 --> 00:08:19,495
I don't think so.

70
00:08:21,233 --> 00:08:23,861
I'll tell you
what I'll do, Jack.

71
00:08:23,935 --> 00:08:27,894
I know some people. Do this for me, I
might be able to get your license back.

72
00:08:27,973 --> 00:08:32,171
- Job pays 10 grand.
- I can't do it.

73
00:08:32,244 --> 00:08:35,873
[Laughs]

74
00:08:35,947 --> 00:08:38,745
Why don't you sleep
on it, Jack?

75
00:08:38,817 --> 00:08:42,947
Seein' how much you like your job, I'd
hate to see you make the wrong decision.

76
00:08:44,589 --> 00:08:48,025
Why don't you check
with me tomorrow?

77
00:08:56,301 --> 00:08:59,395
- Federal Bureau of Investigation.
- [Woman] D.N.A. Is a match.

78
00:08:59,471 --> 00:09:01,405
[Man]
One moment, I'll check.

79
00:09:01,473 --> 00:09:04,442
Today!
Today.

80
00:09:04,509 --> 00:09:07,376
- Excuse me, Holly, is this the file?
- Yes. That's it. Yeah.

81
00:09:07,446 --> 00:09:10,210
From now on you'll be working
with A.T.F. On this.

82
00:09:10,282 --> 00:09:13,080
With all due respect,
I know we've had our setbacks,

83
00:09:13,151 --> 00:09:16,712
but the A.T.F. Directly interfered
with our operation.

84
00:09:16,788 --> 00:09:19,951
- What happened was their fault.
- I'm hearing your defensive
voice again.

85
00:09:20,025 --> 00:09:23,290
- I am not being defensive!
- You say that whenever
you're getting defensive, Allen.

86
00:09:23,362 --> 00:09:25,296
You want me to be defensive.
All right.

87
00:09:25,364 --> 00:09:28,731
You might see yourself
as all over the 6:00 news on this thing,

88
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:31,826
but the reality is, you're putting
a serious operation at risk.

89
00:09:31,903 --> 00:09:34,667
Now, I'm hearing some very real
masculinity issues.

90
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:37,800
What the hell's
the matter with you?

91
00:09:37,876 --> 00:09:42,711
We've got a lead on another shipment.
We don't need this interference.

92
00:09:42,781 --> 00:09:45,682
Allen, this is
hardly my call, okay?

93
00:09:45,751 --> 00:09:49,983
Coordinate your efforts with Agent
McClaren, and you'll both report to me.

94
00:09:50,055 --> 00:09:53,354
That's the way
it's gonna be!

95
00:09:53,425 --> 00:09:57,396
[Man] I agree with you.
Very little I can do.

96
00:09:57,529 --> 00:09:59,520
- [Timer Buzzes]
- Tracy, dinner!

97
00:09:59,598 --> 00:10:04,968
- Hi. What are we having?
- Only the absolute best, homemade.

98
00:10:05,036 --> 00:10:07,300
- Did you wash your hands?
- Yep.

99
00:10:07,372 --> 00:10:09,363
- How's practice?
- Good!

100
00:10:09,441 --> 00:10:11,705
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

101
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:15,008
Dad, can you help me
with my foul shots tomorrow?

102
00:10:15,080 --> 00:10:18,538
- We have a game on Friday.
- Yeah. You bet.

103
00:10:19,951 --> 00:10:24,183
- I'm not missin' this one.
- [Giggles]

104
00:10:24,256 --> 00:10:26,747
[Crickets Chirping]

105
00:10:30,996 --> 00:10:35,626
You truly are gorgeous.
You know that?

106
00:10:45,644 --> 00:10:47,578
- Do you remember...
- Hmm?

107
00:10:47,646 --> 00:10:51,138
- That night at Grover's Point?
- Mm-hmm.

108
00:10:51,216 --> 00:10:54,151
The thunder...
and the lightning...

109
00:10:54,219 --> 00:10:57,586
- [Together] And the candles.
- [Laughing]

110
00:11:00,826 --> 00:11:03,954
[Whispering]
Be right back.

111
00:11:23,949 --> 00:11:27,146
Foreclosure.

112
00:11:36,094 --> 00:11:38,562
[Whispering]
I wanted to tell you, but I...

113
00:11:38,630 --> 00:11:41,292
thought you should have
some breathing room first.

114
00:11:44,069 --> 00:11:47,095
$9,000?

115
00:11:47,172 --> 00:11:50,141
After they cut my hours,
I just couldn't make ends meet.

116
00:11:50,208 --> 00:11:53,974
God! Melanie, why didn't
you say something? I could've...

117
00:11:54,045 --> 00:11:57,606
You could've what, Jack?
You were inside.

118
00:12:00,385 --> 00:12:03,877
Look, we'll rent a place back in Newark
till we can get back on our feet.

119
00:12:03,955 --> 00:12:07,584
- We'll make it work.
- No. No.

120
00:12:07,659 --> 00:12:10,093
We moved out of Newark,
so Tracy could have a yard...

121
00:12:10,161 --> 00:12:12,959
and go to a school without
metal detectors in the halls.

122
00:12:13,031 --> 00:12:15,022
We are not going back!

123
00:12:15,100 --> 00:12:18,399
I worked my ass off for this.
I'm not gonna let us lose this house.

124
00:12:18,470 --> 00:12:22,236
Jack, even with what we both
make, we are too far behind.

125
00:12:24,609 --> 00:12:29,376
I was offered
a job today... driving.

126
00:12:31,149 --> 00:12:35,813
One load.
Atlanta to here. Cash.

127
00:12:35,887 --> 00:12:39,220
Melanie, I'll make enough
money to get us out of this.

128
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:44,160
The last time you said one
more load then we'd be okay,

129
00:12:44,229 --> 00:12:46,163
we weren't.

130
00:12:49,401 --> 00:12:52,666
I can't go
through that again.

131
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:04,981
[Thunderclap]

132
00:13:09,187 --> 00:13:11,519
[Chattering On Radio]

133
00:13:14,993 --> 00:13:18,019
[Animal Growling]

134
00:13:23,802 --> 00:13:26,999
[Animal Snarling]

135
00:13:29,140 --> 00:13:31,233
[Dog Snarling]

136
00:13:34,346 --> 00:13:36,576
[Tires Screeching]

137
00:13:36,648 --> 00:13:38,582
- [Thunderclap]
- [Panting]

138
00:14:03,975 --> 00:14:05,977
[Jet Engines Roaring]

139
00:14:05,977 --> 00:14:06,409
[Jet Engines Roaring]

140
00:14:21,126 --> 00:14:23,287
[Woman]
(music) Tryin' to make a livin' (music)

141
00:14:23,361 --> 00:14:26,489
(music) That's the bottom line (music)

142
00:14:26,564 --> 00:14:31,433
- (music) It ain't easy tryin' to
stretch a nickel into a dime (music)
- Appreciate it. Y'all take care.

143
00:14:31,503 --> 00:14:37,567
(music) Scratchin' for a dollar
workin' for the man (music)

144
00:14:37,642 --> 00:14:42,409
(music) Half goes to the landlord
and half to Uncle Sam (music)

145
00:14:42,480 --> 00:14:47,782
(music) I can't get no consolation
I don't get no faith again (music)

146
00:14:47,852 --> 00:14:51,879
- (music) I can't get no satisfaction
and my tractor (music)
- King me. King me.

147
00:14:51,956 --> 00:14:53,685
- (music) Ain't gettin' no traction (music)
- Earl back?

148
00:14:53,758 --> 00:14:55,191
[Man]
No.

149
00:14:55,260 --> 00:14:57,990
I need them damn
Sunday throwaways.

150
00:14:58,063 --> 00:15:00,224
You gonna play, or you gonna
do somethin' else?

151
00:15:00,298 --> 00:15:04,166
- You the driver from New Jersey?
- That's me.

152
00:15:04,235 --> 00:15:07,898
- You got a name?
- Jack Crews.

153
00:15:07,972 --> 00:15:10,338
[Hammering]

154
00:15:10,408 --> 00:15:14,276
"And they shall beat
their swords into plowshares..."

155
00:15:14,345 --> 00:15:17,143
Isaiah 2, verse 4.

156
00:15:17,215 --> 00:15:20,082
You read your Bible?

157
00:15:20,151 --> 00:15:23,643
- Probably not as much as I should.
- You try and lead a good life?

158
00:15:23,722 --> 00:15:25,690
When I can.

159
00:15:26,758 --> 00:15:28,692
That's the most
important thing.

160
00:15:30,195 --> 00:15:32,356
- [Engine Whining]
- Excuse me, Mr. Crews.

161
00:15:35,700 --> 00:15:38,168
- Where have you been?
- Puttin' her through her paces.

162
00:15:38,236 --> 00:15:40,170
This ain't
a damn NASCAR rally.

163
00:15:40,238 --> 00:15:42,172
Did you get
my Sunday throwaways?

164
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:45,505
- You know, it slipped my mind.
- It slipped your mind?

165
00:15:45,577 --> 00:15:48,944
Did you know there's coupons for 50
cents off luncheon meats at Winn-Dixie?

166
00:15:49,013 --> 00:15:52,505
I ask you to do
one simple thing.

167
00:15:54,953 --> 00:15:57,421
Mr. Cutler
sent us a driver.

168
00:15:58,389 --> 00:16:01,290
Earl. Jack Crews.

169
00:16:01,359 --> 00:16:03,224
You'll have to forgive
Earl's manners.

170
00:16:03,294 --> 00:16:06,752
He was hopin' he'd get to drive.
[Chuckles]

171
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:11,430
- Uh, I'm not takin' that.
- What?

172
00:16:11,503 --> 00:16:14,404
It's brand-spankin' new.

173
00:16:14,472 --> 00:16:16,497
I don't need
that kind of attention.

174
00:16:16,574 --> 00:16:20,977
Junior, come down here
and show Jack Crews a tractor...

175
00:16:21,045 --> 00:16:24,378
that's more to his likin'.

176
00:16:24,449 --> 00:16:26,508
Come on.

177
00:16:29,354 --> 00:16:33,848
I think Mr. Cutler suspects something.
He sent down a new driver.

178
00:16:33,925 --> 00:16:36,723
It don't make a damn bit of difference,
Red. Our deal's with you.

179
00:16:36,795 --> 00:16:38,956
I know that.

180
00:16:39,030 --> 00:16:42,522
Things are gettin' more complicated now.
I'm gonna need some more cash.

181
00:16:42,600 --> 00:16:44,795
You listen to me.
6:00 tonight with that truck...

182
00:16:44,869 --> 00:16:48,100
or cash'll be
the last thing you need.

183
00:16:48,173 --> 00:16:53,042
- So, what's it got in it?
- 3406 "Cat," turbo-ed,
four and a quarter,

184
00:16:53,111 --> 00:16:56,672
- Fuller-Eaton ten-speed, pro-shift.
- Got a Jake brake?

185
00:16:56,748 --> 00:16:59,808
Yep.

186
00:16:59,884 --> 00:17:02,444
- How are the brakes?
- New. Put 'em on myself.

187
00:17:02,520 --> 00:17:07,958
- And the rubber?
- Almost new. Ain't no recaps.

188
00:17:08,026 --> 00:17:11,189
All right. Fire her up.

189
00:17:26,344 --> 00:17:30,405
- Earl's gonna be riding with ya.
- What do ya mean,
he's gonna be riding with me?

190
00:17:30,481 --> 00:17:34,110
Somebody has to drive
that tractor home.

191
00:17:34,185 --> 00:17:36,881
Right as rain.

192
00:17:40,225 --> 00:17:42,659
Sonny's here.
I guess we can hit it.

193
00:17:45,196 --> 00:17:47,130
You're late.

194
00:17:47,198 --> 00:17:50,895
Yeah. Yeah, I know.
I may be late, but I'm always on time.

195
00:17:50,969 --> 00:17:54,336
- Hey, Wes. [Laughs]
- Hey, Earl.

196
00:17:54,405 --> 00:17:57,397
- Who's that?
- He's drivin'.

197
00:17:57,475 --> 00:18:00,342
- Since when?
- Since an hour ago.

198
00:18:00,411 --> 00:18:01,746
- Came down from the top.
- From the top of what?

199
00:18:01,746 --> 00:18:02,610
- Came down from the top.
- From the top of what?

200
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:04,614
You make him seem like
he's goddamned Moses.

201
00:18:04,682 --> 00:18:08,277
- Don't you take
the Lord's name in vain.
- I'm goddamned sorry.

202
00:18:08,352 --> 00:18:13,016
You gonna be sorry. If you don't like
it, Sonny, you can get out right now.

203
00:18:13,090 --> 00:18:17,959
What I don't like is you, him
or anybody else changing the plans
every time I turn around.

204
00:18:18,028 --> 00:18:19,928
That's what I don't like.

205
00:18:19,997 --> 00:18:23,057
- I'm Sonny.
- And I'm Wes.

206
00:18:23,134 --> 00:18:25,534
And I'm Jack Crews.

207
00:18:25,603 --> 00:18:29,471
We'll be cruisin' right behind ya.
Cruisin' behind "The Crews."

208
00:18:29,540 --> 00:18:31,633
What do ya mean,
you'll be right behind me?

209
00:18:31,709 --> 00:18:34,576
- [Red] Protection.
- Protection from what?

210
00:18:34,645 --> 00:18:38,809
It's policy. We send
a car with every truck.

211
00:18:40,751 --> 00:18:43,219
Come on. Let's do it.

212
00:18:59,870 --> 00:19:01,997
[Dog Barking]

213
00:19:06,510 --> 00:19:10,810
- This your dog?
- Tiny ain't nobody's dog but his own.

214
00:19:10,881 --> 00:19:13,076
Easy, boy.

215
00:19:13,150 --> 00:19:18,053
Toilets. Can you believe it?
Five-gallon flush.

216
00:19:19,356 --> 00:19:24,191
- Wanna look any closer?
- I'm just here to drive.

217
00:19:30,167 --> 00:19:34,501
(music) I was born on a bus
they say goin' south (music)

218
00:19:34,572 --> 00:19:39,908
(music) Left at a truck stop
I never knew my mother (music)

219
00:19:39,977 --> 00:19:45,711
(music) And ever since
the highway's been my home (music)

220
00:19:45,783 --> 00:19:50,277
(music) Like a restless wind
I keep movin' on and I (music)

221
00:19:50,354 --> 00:19:56,486
(music) Can't seem to stay
in one place too long (music)

222
00:19:56,560 --> 00:20:00,462
(music) I'm a road man (music)

223
00:20:00,531 --> 00:20:06,697
(music) Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah (music)

224
00:20:11,442 --> 00:20:13,603
Over there,
you have your starter.

225
00:20:13,677 --> 00:20:19,115
Down there's your clutch,
brake, go pedal.

226
00:20:19,183 --> 00:20:23,483
- Thanks for reminding me.
- Let's see what ya got.

227
00:20:35,566 --> 00:20:37,056
[Engine Starts]

228
00:20:46,277 --> 00:20:50,407
- [Air Whooshes]
- [Sighs]

229
00:20:55,219 --> 00:20:57,949
[Sighs]

230
00:20:59,456 --> 00:21:03,324
[Engine Shudders, Stalls]

231
00:21:03,394 --> 00:21:05,521
I thought
you could drive.

232
00:21:07,765 --> 00:21:09,699
First time.

233
00:21:22,713 --> 00:21:26,012
This driver comin' down,
does that change things?

234
00:21:26,083 --> 00:21:28,643
You're not plannin' on havin' kids,
are ya, Junior?

235
00:21:28,719 --> 00:21:32,211
I don't know.
Find the right woman, maybe.

236
00:21:32,289 --> 00:21:37,317
- Why?
- 'Cause you suffer from
a sorry-ass lack of balls.

237
00:21:39,430 --> 00:21:42,422
(music) Well, the midnight headlights
blinds you on a rainy night (music)

238
00:21:42,499 --> 00:21:47,402
(music) Steep grade up ahead
Slow me down, makin' no time (music)

239
00:21:47,471 --> 00:21:50,998
(music) But I gotta keep rollin' (music)

240
00:21:51,075 --> 00:21:54,374
(music) Those windshield wipers
slappin' out a tempo (music)

241
00:21:54,445 --> 00:21:58,939
(music) Keepin' perfect rhythm
with the song on the radio (music)

242
00:21:59,016 --> 00:22:03,453
(music) Yeah, I gotta keep rollin' (music)

243
00:22:03,520 --> 00:22:08,617
(music) Ooh, I'm drivin'
my life away (music)

244
00:22:08,692 --> 00:22:11,923
(music) Lookin' for a better way (music)

245
00:22:11,996 --> 00:22:15,056
(music) For me (music)

246
00:22:15,132 --> 00:22:18,590
"Virgo: Today's
the day to begin...

247
00:22:18,669 --> 00:22:22,161
a business relationship
with a new friend."

248
00:22:22,239 --> 00:22:24,173
Guess you're
my new friend.

249
00:22:29,980 --> 00:22:33,507
(music) Well, the truck stop cutie
comin' on to me (music)

250
00:22:33,584 --> 00:22:36,985
(music) Tried to talk me into a ride
Said I wouldn't be sorry (music)

251
00:22:37,054 --> 00:22:40,285
We in the middle of committing a felony.
That's what you want to do, litter?

252
00:22:40,357 --> 00:22:45,158
- We're not committing anything.
We're just following a truck.
- Yeah, right.

253
00:22:45,229 --> 00:22:47,459
- Ya wanna play Pididdle?
- Pi... what?

254
00:22:47,531 --> 00:22:50,796
Pididdle... Ya see a car
with one headlight, you yell "Pididdle."

255
00:22:50,868 --> 00:22:53,234
First one to yell wins.

256
00:22:53,303 --> 00:22:58,502
- It's daylight, Wes.
- Ya got a point.

257
00:22:58,575 --> 00:23:04,411
[Laughs]
I got it. Yes.

258
00:23:04,481 --> 00:23:07,314
This is what I do.
This is my passion.

259
00:23:07,384 --> 00:23:09,375
I'm a...
I'm a songwriter.

260
00:23:09,453 --> 00:23:11,683
That's what I do.

261
00:23:11,755 --> 00:23:13,916
Listen to this.

262
00:23:13,991 --> 00:23:18,860
(music) Do you still read my horoscope
in the paper every mornin' (music)

263
00:23:18,929 --> 00:23:21,727
(music) To see exactly what
I'm gonna do (music)

264
00:23:21,799 --> 00:23:28,602
(music) Do you still read my horoscope
in the paper every mornin' (music)

265
00:23:28,672 --> 00:23:34,201
(music) To see if I'll be
comin' home to you (music)

266
00:23:34,278 --> 00:23:36,212
What do ya think?

267
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:40,808
Uh, l... I don't listen
to very much country music.

268
00:23:40,884 --> 00:23:43,409
Well, I do.
Take my word for it.

269
00:23:43,487 --> 00:23:45,421
This is the beginning
of a good song.

270
00:23:45,489 --> 00:23:49,016
See, a good song has to have
a good hook. That's what it's all about.

271
00:23:49,093 --> 00:23:54,463
You reach out and...
and you grab with "horoscope."
See, you give 'em the twist...

272
00:23:54,531 --> 00:23:57,227
- Pull over, would ya?
I gotta take a leak.
- Again?

273
00:23:57,301 --> 00:24:01,704
I got a bladder
the size of a pea.

274
00:24:01,772 --> 00:24:05,970
Breaker 1-9 from 10-36.

275
00:24:06,043 --> 00:24:08,034
What do you want?

276
00:24:08,112 --> 00:24:10,842
[Sonny]
Wes has to drain his lily.

277
00:24:13,984 --> 00:24:16,384
Think I'll hit
the head too.

278
00:24:19,756 --> 00:24:22,054
I'm gonna see if they
got any books on tape.

279
00:24:23,861 --> 00:24:29,322
All that stuff about Moses and all that.
That wasn't personal, you understand.

280
00:24:29,399 --> 00:24:32,493
- No problem.
- I just wish for once these clowns...

281
00:24:32,569 --> 00:24:36,198
- would stick to the plan,
you know what I'm sayin'?
- I hear you.

282
00:24:37,274 --> 00:24:39,208
Hello!

283
00:24:39,276 --> 00:24:44,908
- [Chuckles] He... Hello. Come to Papa!
- In your dreams, Wes.

284
00:24:48,418 --> 00:24:53,481
(music) He's been gone
for ten long days (music)

285
00:24:53,557 --> 00:24:57,755
(music) Burnin' up that interstate (music)

286
00:24:57,828 --> 00:25:02,925
(music) He's got a run
from coast to coast (music)

287
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:07,596
- (music) I got one more night to go (music)
- See, I told you we could play
Pididdle in the day.

288
00:25:07,671 --> 00:25:11,505
- What?
- Pididdle, right behind us.

289
00:25:13,644 --> 00:25:15,111
- [Gun Cocking]
- Oh!

290
00:25:17,981 --> 00:25:20,677
What the...

291
00:25:24,454 --> 00:25:26,945
- [Grunts]
- [Glass Shatters]

292
00:25:33,363 --> 00:25:36,059
- [Tires Screeching]
- [Horn Blares]

293
00:25:36,133 --> 00:25:39,296
Ah... Aah...

294
00:25:59,223 --> 00:26:01,453
[Screams]

295
00:26:11,235 --> 00:26:12,759
Oh-oh.

296
00:26:15,572 --> 00:26:17,506
[Both Grunt]

297
00:26:24,013 --> 00:26:26,914
That's D.W. And Leroy
from Red's place.

298
00:26:26,983 --> 00:26:30,350
What the hell
are they doin'?

299
00:26:30,419 --> 00:26:33,149
Now, we got ya.

300
00:26:43,666 --> 00:26:45,861
[Grunts]

301
00:26:52,041 --> 00:26:55,670
- [Grunts]
- [Engine Revving]

302
00:27:04,820 --> 00:27:08,517
- That Red's truck?
- He's tryin' to hijack the load.

303
00:27:08,591 --> 00:27:10,923
Good ol'
Southern hospitality.

304
00:27:16,565 --> 00:27:19,090
Crews?

305
00:27:21,203 --> 00:27:23,535
Huh? Jeez!

306
00:27:25,474 --> 00:27:27,339
What are ya doin'?

307
00:27:29,011 --> 00:27:30,979
[Grunting]

308
00:27:31,047 --> 00:27:33,982
[Grunts]
Oh...

309
00:27:35,284 --> 00:27:37,309
Son of a bitch!

310
00:27:44,927 --> 00:27:48,158
What the hell you waitin' on?
Move it! Move it!

311
00:27:48,230 --> 00:27:51,222
Let's go! Let's go!
Get out of that truck! Come on!

312
00:27:54,303 --> 00:27:59,263
I should've seen this comin'. For all
his talk of Jesus, Red is a greedy man.

313
00:28:08,517 --> 00:28:09,882
[Grunting]

314
00:28:12,822 --> 00:28:14,983
[Tires Screeching]

315
00:28:19,929 --> 00:28:24,957
Sonny, next time he backs off,
floor it. Can you do that?

316
00:28:25,034 --> 00:28:28,162
Okay, I'm gonna try!

317
00:28:28,237 --> 00:28:31,070
Watch out!

318
00:28:31,140 --> 00:28:33,836
- Sonny, now!
- Go! Go! Go!

319
00:28:37,113 --> 00:28:39,673
[Tires Screeching]

320
00:28:51,360 --> 00:28:56,730
- Yeah. You can drive.
- It's comin' back to me.

321
00:29:07,510 --> 00:29:11,446
Damn! Look what he did
to my car, man!

322
00:29:11,514 --> 00:29:13,448
Can't believe this!

323
00:29:13,516 --> 00:29:16,576
Will you look at this!

324
00:29:16,652 --> 00:29:22,557
If people are willing
to kill me to get this load,
I ought to know exactly what they want.

325
00:29:35,671 --> 00:29:39,835
"The gates of Babylon
shall not be shut."

326
00:29:39,909 --> 00:29:42,104
That son of a bitch can drive.

327
00:29:42,178 --> 00:29:45,375
[Red] We're gonna have to work
a little harder to get that load.

328
00:29:45,448 --> 00:29:51,353
- Maybe we ought to give up.
- Junior, never underestimate
the power of prayer.

329
00:29:55,324 --> 00:30:00,921
- [Barking]
- Hey, Tiny. Rough ride, wasn't it, boy?

330
00:30:24,019 --> 00:30:25,953
What a surprise.

331
00:30:27,790 --> 00:30:32,386
AK-47, Chinese assault rifles.
Twelve rounds per second.

332
00:30:32,461 --> 00:30:37,489
- One tug on this baby,
and it'll cut you in half.
- Box it up.

333
00:30:48,944 --> 00:30:51,811
- [Man On Phone] Yeah, Frank Cutler.
- Yeah, it's Crews.

334
00:30:51,881 --> 00:30:54,111
Hey, good to hear from ya, Jack.
How's everything?

335
00:30:54,183 --> 00:30:56,879
Well, I did have a little
run-in with your friend, Red.

336
00:30:56,952 --> 00:30:59,079
It seems he's tryin'
to hijack your load.

337
00:30:59,155 --> 00:31:03,819
- Is the load okay?
- You didn't tell me I'd be
hauling illegal artillery.

338
00:31:03,893 --> 00:31:05,827
Well, the truth is, Jack,
if you wanted to know...

339
00:31:05,895 --> 00:31:08,125
what was in the back of
that truck, you would've asked.

340
00:31:08,197 --> 00:31:12,429
The reason I hired you, Crews, is 'cause
I knew you could get the job done.

341
00:31:12,501 --> 00:31:15,436
But if you can't handle Red,
you tell me now.

342
00:31:15,504 --> 00:31:17,495
I want those guns... tonight!

343
00:31:17,573 --> 00:31:19,632
Now, you just go back and get
in that truck and do the job...

344
00:31:19,708 --> 00:31:22,074
I'm paying you to do, because
I don't think your parole officer...

345
00:31:22,144 --> 00:31:24,612
is gonna be nearly as
understanding as I am.

346
00:31:24,680 --> 00:31:28,207
- You understand what I'm sayin', Jack?
- I'll do what I have to.

347
00:31:29,885 --> 00:31:32,285
- [Sighs]
- [Phone Beeps]

348
00:31:35,691 --> 00:31:37,716
This guy's
gonna be trouble.

349
00:31:38,794 --> 00:31:41,820
- All right, Tiny.
- They hit us once,

350
00:31:41,897 --> 00:31:44,388
they might try it again.

351
00:31:44,466 --> 00:31:48,027
You know, I was thinkin',
we could switch to l-85.

352
00:31:48,103 --> 00:31:50,731
There's a turnoff
about 20 miles up.

353
00:31:50,806 --> 00:31:54,242
That way, if Red comes back,
we won't be where he thinks we'll be.

354
00:31:55,744 --> 00:32:00,977
- Sonny, you ride with me.
- Let's do it.

355
00:32:01,050 --> 00:32:04,884
Crews? Wait a minute!
You think I was in on this?

356
00:32:04,954 --> 00:32:07,855
- Crossed my mind. Yeah.
- I wasn't. I swear.

357
00:32:07,923 --> 00:32:11,154
Red never tells me anything.
You can ask anybody.

358
00:32:11,227 --> 00:32:13,161
Earl, you got that right.

359
00:32:13,229 --> 00:32:16,687
Hey, man, they were
shootin' at me too!

360
00:32:16,765 --> 00:32:19,427
You ever thought about bein'
a professional singer?

361
00:32:20,436 --> 00:32:22,666
Don't.

362
00:32:22,738 --> 00:32:24,729
Did I miss something?

363
00:32:24,807 --> 00:32:26,741
Get in the car, Wes.

364
00:32:29,345 --> 00:32:32,041
- Tried to sing you songs?
- Ugh...

365
00:32:32,114 --> 00:32:35,572
Well, no wonder you want
the pleasure of my company.

366
00:32:41,156 --> 00:32:43,147
[Engine Revs]

367
00:32:47,329 --> 00:32:49,559
[Tires Screeching]

368
00:32:51,467 --> 00:32:53,435
[Ford] Okay, they're
on the move again.

369
00:32:53,502 --> 00:32:56,164
First sign of trouble,
I'm bringing them in.

370
00:32:56,238 --> 00:33:01,107
- There's over $3 million in
automatic weapons on that truck.
- I know that.

371
00:33:01,176 --> 00:33:04,441
Then you know the array of tragedy
those guns are going to inflict when...

372
00:33:04,513 --> 00:33:07,710
- they hit the streets of Jersey?
- I want the man
who puts them on the streets.

373
00:33:07,783 --> 00:33:10,650
We don't take him out,
he'll have $3 million in automatic...

374
00:33:10,719 --> 00:33:13,381
weapons comin' up from Georgia
this time next week.

375
00:33:13,455 --> 00:33:17,186
I mean, that might keep you in a job,
but it's not the solution.

376
00:33:17,259 --> 00:33:20,524
Guy driving is Jack Philip Crews.
Did two years in Bayside.

377
00:33:20,596 --> 00:33:23,895
That sounds like just the kind of man
you want hauling a load of artillery.

378
00:33:23,966 --> 00:33:27,197
No priors. He was released three weeks
ago, early parole for good behavior.

379
00:33:27,269 --> 00:33:30,102
- Looks like he's just the driver.
- What'd he do his time for?

380
00:33:30,172 --> 00:33:33,164
- Vehicular manslaughter.
- Thank you.

381
00:33:36,312 --> 00:33:39,839
[Ringing, Beeps]

382
00:33:39,915 --> 00:33:41,849
- Crews residence.
- Hey, little one.

383
00:33:41,917 --> 00:33:43,851
- Dad!
- So, how was school?

384
00:33:43,919 --> 00:33:47,719
Great. We had a half a day.
Are you still gonna help me
with my free throws tonight?

385
00:33:47,790 --> 00:33:50,418
Well, I, uh...
I can't tonight, honey.

386
00:33:50,492 --> 00:33:53,120
If I wanna buy you
those high-tops, I gotta work late.

387
00:33:53,195 --> 00:33:55,425
But, no way
I'm missin' your game.

388
00:33:55,497 --> 00:33:59,593
- So, can I speak to your mom?
- Yeah.

389
00:33:59,668 --> 00:34:02,660
- Mom.
- Go get your homework started, okay?

390
00:34:02,738 --> 00:34:04,672
Okay.

391
00:34:04,740 --> 00:34:09,439
- Jack? Where are you?
- North Carolina.

392
00:34:09,511 --> 00:34:12,207
Look, I know you didn't
want me to do this but...

393
00:34:12,281 --> 00:34:16,274
Melanie, I can't
let us lose that house.

394
00:34:16,352 --> 00:34:19,879
I think we both know this is about
more than the house, Jack.

395
00:34:19,955 --> 00:34:22,287
It's about you.

396
00:34:22,358 --> 00:34:27,796
[Sighs] Well, I'll be home as soon
as I can. I love you.

397
00:34:29,765 --> 00:34:31,790
Be careful.

398
00:34:34,870 --> 00:34:36,804
[Phone Beeps]

399
00:34:38,974 --> 00:34:40,965
[Beeps]

400
00:35:02,331 --> 00:35:06,461
- How long you been drivin' trucks?
- Since I was 18.

401
00:35:06,535 --> 00:35:09,834
- Not much for school, huh?
- Had to make a living.

402
00:35:11,873 --> 00:35:14,103
I was gonna be a football player
before I screwed up my knee.

403
00:35:14,176 --> 00:35:17,270
So, now you run guns
instead of footballs.

404
00:35:19,014 --> 00:35:21,414
I'm gonna make me
some serious money.

405
00:35:21,483 --> 00:35:25,249
Buy a house on the lake.
Hell, I might even buy me a lake.

406
00:35:26,822 --> 00:35:30,314
Find a nice little honey,
settle down.

407
00:35:30,392 --> 00:35:35,193
- How about you? You got big dreams?
- I'm workin' on it.

408
00:35:35,263 --> 00:35:37,231
[Crews]
Oh, shi...

409
00:35:37,299 --> 00:35:40,097
What's wrong?

410
00:35:40,168 --> 00:35:43,137
There's a weigh station
on both of these roads.

411
00:35:43,205 --> 00:35:47,005
- One of 'em is bound to be open.
- So, we got a 50-50 chance.

412
00:35:47,075 --> 00:35:51,341
- That's right.
- Earl said take 85.

413
00:36:01,723 --> 00:36:05,887
Where the hell is he goin'?
I told him not to take 26.

414
00:36:12,167 --> 00:36:14,328
[Sighs]

415
00:36:23,612 --> 00:36:27,605
[Man] Okay, let's see
your next set of axles.

416
00:36:27,683 --> 00:36:32,279
Hold it there.

417
00:36:32,354 --> 00:36:34,288
Pull forward, driver.

418
00:36:34,356 --> 00:36:36,187
Next two.

419
00:36:43,265 --> 00:36:45,199
- [Engine Idling]
- Gonna go grab a smoke.

420
00:36:56,278 --> 00:36:59,679
Pull forward, driver.

421
00:37:12,728 --> 00:37:14,662
- How are you, sir?
- All right. How are you?

422
00:37:14,730 --> 00:37:18,791
- Okay.
- You know you got
a headlight out up there?

423
00:37:18,867 --> 00:37:21,358
- What'd ya do to your front end?
- She was that way when I picked her up.

424
00:37:21,436 --> 00:37:24,462
It's not my usual rig.

425
00:37:24,539 --> 00:37:26,837
Pull up, driver.
Next two.

426
00:37:32,380 --> 00:37:34,610
Hold it there.

427
00:37:34,683 --> 00:37:37,880
[Air Brakes Hissing]

428
00:37:41,556 --> 00:37:44,582
Hey, uh... Bobby Lewis
still work here?

429
00:37:44,659 --> 00:37:47,492
- Big guy. Wrestler.
- You talkin' about Pooh Bear.

430
00:37:47,562 --> 00:37:51,328
- Pooh Bear... Yeah.
- No. He took a private job...

431
00:37:51,399 --> 00:37:54,129
down in Orlando
about a year ago now.

432
00:37:54,202 --> 00:37:56,636
So, you haven't made
this run in a while, have you?

433
00:37:56,705 --> 00:37:58,764
No, sir, not in
a couple of years.

434
00:38:00,475 --> 00:38:02,670
Pull forward, driver.

435
00:38:02,744 --> 00:38:05,679
[Engine Revs]

436
00:38:07,616 --> 00:38:10,210
[Air Brakes Hiss]

437
00:38:15,457 --> 00:38:18,756
- You're right at the limit.
- Aw, you know these guys.

438
00:38:18,827 --> 00:38:21,193
They try to ring
every dollar from a load.

439
00:38:21,263 --> 00:38:25,393
- You pull for this outfit often?
- Not when I can help it.

440
00:38:25,467 --> 00:38:28,300
Got a load of bathroom
fixtures, huh?

441
00:38:28,370 --> 00:38:31,203
Yeah. Toilets.
[Chuckles]

442
00:38:33,975 --> 00:38:36,102
I tell you what. Why don't
you pull up right over there?

443
00:38:36,178 --> 00:38:38,237
And I'm just gonna take
a quick look in the back.

444
00:38:38,313 --> 00:38:40,713
All right. Will do.

445
00:38:58,667 --> 00:39:02,603
Yeah. Yeah.
I'll get back with you later.

446
00:39:02,671 --> 00:39:06,004
Who you talkin' to?

447
00:39:06,074 --> 00:39:08,235
My mother.

448
00:39:08,310 --> 00:39:10,801
Your mother, my ass.

449
00:39:10,879 --> 00:39:13,848
She's in a cancer ward
at Good Samaritan in Philly.

450
00:39:13,915 --> 00:39:17,612
You wanna give 'em a call?
Ask for Nadine Boxer.

451
00:39:17,686 --> 00:39:22,453
Don't keep her on the phone too long.
She doesn't have a lot of strength left.

452
00:39:24,392 --> 00:39:28,158
Here.
Good Samaritan.

453
