689
01:00:31,357 --> 01:00:35,521
Your ass is mine! God!

690
01:00:41,033 --> 01:00:45,026
Sonny, can ya hear me?
Sonny! Hang in there!

691
01:00:47,039 --> 01:00:50,065
Stay with us, Sonny!
Come on! Come on!

692
01:00:50,209 --> 01:00:55,511
[Sonny Groaning]

693
01:00:55,581 --> 01:00:57,515
- How's he doin'?
- He's bad!

694
01:00:57,583 --> 01:01:01,314
- I'm cold.
- You just hang in.

695
01:01:01,387 --> 01:01:04,220
I'm gonna take care
of you, Crews.

696
01:01:09,762 --> 01:01:13,289
I'm gonna take care
of you, man.

697
01:01:13,366 --> 01:01:16,130
You just stick with me
when this goes down, okay?

698
01:01:16,202 --> 01:01:18,670
When what goes down?

699
01:01:18,738 --> 01:01:22,469
[Panting]
They know where we are.

700
01:01:22,542 --> 01:01:24,533
I'm F.B.I.

701
01:01:26,812 --> 01:01:30,043
I know they got
your wife and kid,

702
01:01:30,116 --> 01:01:32,175
but you got a truckfull
of death here, man.

703
01:01:34,654 --> 01:01:37,350
And this shit
has got to stop.

704
01:01:47,400 --> 01:01:49,334
I know that, Sonny.

705
01:02:14,760 --> 01:02:16,694
[Sizzles]

706
01:02:27,940 --> 01:02:30,431
[Sonny's Voice]
I'm gonna take care of you, Crews.

707
01:02:30,509 --> 01:02:32,443
Box it up.

708
01:02:32,511 --> 01:02:35,105
[Sonny' Voice] When this goes down,
you just stick with me, okay?

709
01:02:35,181 --> 01:02:38,582
They know where we are.

710
01:02:38,651 --> 01:02:41,484
I'm F.B.I.

711
01:03:22,828 --> 01:03:27,265
(music) [Earl Humming]

712
01:03:35,341 --> 01:03:39,539
(music) [Humming Continues]

713
01:03:47,687 --> 01:03:52,181
(music) Please believe
you're all I ever wanted (music)

714
01:03:53,626 --> 01:03:58,563
(music) If you should leave
I don't know what I'd do (music)

715
01:04:00,099 --> 01:04:05,628
(music) I'd be like a child
afraid of darkness (music)

716
01:04:05,805 --> 01:04:10,469
(music) The greatest fear I have
is losing you (music)

717
01:04:13,779 --> 01:04:16,009
[Thunder Rumbles]

718
01:04:16,082 --> 01:04:21,213
Hey, Earl, you know that thing I said
back there about you being a singer?

719
01:04:21,287 --> 01:04:24,916
I'm really sorry.
I didn't mean it.

720
01:04:26,125 --> 01:04:28,059
Thanks.

721
01:04:30,696 --> 01:04:32,891
Hey, where'd you learn
the gunpowder trick?

722
01:04:34,800 --> 01:04:37,064
I heard about it
in prison.

723
01:04:37,136 --> 01:04:39,730
You were in prison?

724
01:04:39,805 --> 01:04:43,070
Yes, sir, two years.

725
01:04:43,142 --> 01:04:46,441
- [Earl] For what?
- Vehicular manslaughter.

726
01:04:46,512 --> 01:04:51,916
- That's comforting to know.
- You saw the dog, didn't you?

727
01:04:54,153 --> 01:04:57,088
- What dog?
- The black dog.

728
01:04:57,156 --> 01:04:59,920
You mean like
the Led Zeppelin song?

729
01:04:59,992 --> 01:05:03,086
No, Crews knows what
I'm talkin' about, don't ya?

730
01:05:03,162 --> 01:05:06,620
I've heard truckers
talk about it on the yard.

731
01:05:06,699 --> 01:05:11,295
They say it comes when you've been on
the road too long and pushin' too hard,

732
01:05:11,370 --> 01:05:13,600
when you get greedy.

733
01:05:13,672 --> 01:05:17,574
They say it comes to take
everything away from ya.

734
01:05:17,643 --> 01:05:19,804
And it did.

735
01:05:21,180 --> 01:05:25,378
I was, uh, hauling
a load up from Atlanta...

736
01:05:25,451 --> 01:05:27,612
on my sixth straight
Georgia run.

737
01:05:27,686 --> 01:05:31,213
It was my daughter's birthday, and
I thought I could make it home in time.

738
01:05:31,290 --> 01:05:35,659
[Crews] I was on this long,
dark stretch of l-75...

739
01:05:35,728 --> 01:05:39,129
with nothin' to look at but
the white line when I saw it.

740
01:05:39,198 --> 01:05:42,065
It was in the middle of the road,
comin' straight at me...

741
01:05:42,134 --> 01:05:44,967
with his teeth bared
and red eyes staring.

742
01:05:45,037 --> 01:05:47,904
- [Growling]
- So I swerved to miss him.

743
01:05:47,973 --> 01:05:51,431
- [Tires Screeching]
- Look out!

744
01:05:51,510 --> 01:05:54,240
[Tires Screeching,
Metal Crashing]

745
01:05:55,314 --> 01:05:57,839
And I lost control.

746
01:05:57,917 --> 01:06:00,750
Where do you come up
with this shit?

747
01:06:00,820 --> 01:06:02,947
It's for real, Wes.

748
01:06:03,022 --> 01:06:07,857
Yeah? And I bet you seen O.K. S
and aliens with big eyes.

749
01:06:07,927 --> 01:06:12,762
No, just the black dog.

750
01:06:19,905 --> 01:06:23,500
[Engines Revving]

751
01:06:25,077 --> 01:06:29,707
(music) [Man Singing
Country-Western, Indistinct]

752
01:06:32,251 --> 01:06:36,381
Uh, yeah, is this the F.B.I.?

753
01:06:36,455 --> 01:06:40,585
Okay, listen, I need to talk to an agent
about a gunrunning investigation,

754
01:06:40,659 --> 01:06:43,389
Atlanta to New Jersey.

755
01:06:43,462 --> 01:06:46,454
I'd rather not say. Just let me talk
to the agent in charge.

756
01:06:46,532 --> 01:06:50,161
Look, your undercover agent is dead,

757
01:06:50,236 --> 01:06:54,696
and I have information
about the shipment he was with.

758
01:06:54,773 --> 01:06:59,073
Sonny. I don't know!
He didn't say.

759
01:06:59,144 --> 01:07:04,514
Look, just let me talk to the agent
in charge of the investigation, please.

760
01:07:04,583 --> 01:07:06,517
Oh, forget it!

761
01:07:09,286 --> 01:07:13,017
(music) Then maybe you
don't understand (music)

762
01:07:13,090 --> 01:07:16,059
(music) Oh, we might never be (music)

763
01:07:16,126 --> 01:07:18,720
Well, it's only gonna
get tougher from here on.

764
01:07:18,795 --> 01:07:22,925
So if anyone wants out,
now is the time.

765
01:07:23,000 --> 01:07:26,026
If I stick with you,
am I gonna get my money?

766
01:07:26,103 --> 01:07:28,594
Probably not.

767
01:07:28,672 --> 01:07:31,732
I got nowhere else to go.

768
01:07:34,411 --> 01:07:37,244
I'm out.

769
01:07:37,314 --> 01:07:40,215
Okay,

770
01:07:40,284 --> 01:07:44,243
but there's one thing
I'd like you to do for me.

771
01:07:47,424 --> 01:07:50,052
Appreciate this, you guys
lettin' me leave and all.

772
01:07:50,127 --> 01:07:52,527
Eat shit, Wes.

773
01:07:52,596 --> 01:07:57,033
Crews, good luck!

774
01:08:10,681 --> 01:08:14,708
(music) I gotta tell her
I was wrong (music)

775
01:08:14,785 --> 01:08:18,744
- (music) I gotta show her I still love her (music)
- Did you ever play Pididdle?

776
01:08:18,822 --> 01:08:23,885
(music) I've been drivin'
all night long (music)

777
01:08:23,961 --> 01:08:27,158
[Beeping]

778
01:08:27,231 --> 01:08:30,166
They're heading south out of Richmond,
back the way they came.

779
01:08:30,234 --> 01:08:33,169
- South?
- Unless you, in your infinite wisdom,

780
01:08:33,237 --> 01:08:36,434
know something which I don't know,
I think now is the time.

781
01:08:36,506 --> 01:08:38,531
I agree with Agent McClaren.
We haven't heard from Sonny,

782
01:08:38,609 --> 01:08:41,077
and for all we know,
they've already made the damn drop.

783
01:08:41,144 --> 01:08:45,080
- All right then! Let's go.
- Damn it.

784
01:08:45,148 --> 01:08:48,276
[Sirens Wailing]

785
01:08:52,389 --> 01:08:55,984
[Man On Bullhorn]
This is the F.B.I.!

786
01:08:56,059 --> 01:08:58,493
Stop your vehicle immediately!

787
01:09:11,808 --> 01:09:13,867
- Get 'em up!
- Get out of the cab!

788
01:09:13,944 --> 01:09:16,003
Out of the cab!
Get out!

789
01:09:16,079 --> 01:09:18,013
- Don't shoot!
- [Ford] Get down! Get down!

790
01:09:18,081 --> 01:09:20,015
Get down! Hands up!
Get down!

791
01:09:20,083 --> 01:09:22,051
Hands up.

792
01:09:23,120 --> 01:09:25,054
It's for you.

793
01:09:30,794 --> 01:09:32,728
This is Ford.

794
01:09:32,796 --> 01:09:36,391
- You the F.B.I.?
- Yeah, that's right.

795
01:09:36,466 --> 01:09:39,629
Okay, if you want your guns,
you listen carefully,

796
01:09:39,703 --> 01:09:41,967
and I'm gonna tell you exactly
what I want you to do.

797
01:09:42,139 --> 01:09:44,699
[Man On TV] Punched it,
and I punched out "B."

798
01:09:44,775 --> 01:09:47,869
[Phone Ringing]

799
01:09:47,944 --> 01:09:49,878
Yeah?

800
01:09:49,946 --> 01:09:54,576
- Where's my family?
- They're right here, watchin' TV.

801
01:09:54,651 --> 01:09:59,384
You know, Jack,
everybody's always complaining
about violence on television.

802
01:09:59,456 --> 01:10:02,482
Violence, violence, violence.
Violence is not the problem.

803
01:10:02,559 --> 01:10:05,392
It's these damn sitcoms.
They lie to everybody.

804
01:10:05,462 --> 01:10:08,090
They tell everyone
that life is nice and easy.

805
01:10:08,165 --> 01:10:10,099
And we both know
that's not true, don't we?

806
01:10:10,167 --> 01:10:12,101
Just let me talk to my wife.

807
01:10:18,508 --> 01:10:20,442
Jack?

808
01:10:20,510 --> 01:10:23,240
- Honey, you all right?
- Yeah, I'm okay.

809
01:10:23,313 --> 01:10:26,680
- Tracy?
- She's fine.

810
01:10:26,750 --> 01:10:30,743
Listen, Melanie, you gotta trust me.
I'm gonna get you out of this, okay?

811
01:10:30,821 --> 01:10:32,755
How you gonna do that, Jack?

812
01:10:34,324 --> 01:10:37,691
I got your guns. You want 'em,
you're gonna have to come get 'em.

813
01:10:37,761 --> 01:10:39,695
Don't you fool
with me, Jack!

814
01:10:39,763 --> 01:10:41,697
You do what
I tell you to do.

815
01:10:41,765 --> 01:10:43,926
I don't wanna say this
in front of your wife,

816
01:10:44,000 --> 01:10:46,594
but if I do not have
my guns by midnight,

817
01:10:46,670 --> 01:10:50,231
I am gonna kill her and the kid,
and I am gonna do it ugly.

818
01:10:50,307 --> 01:10:53,538
No, you're not gonna do that, because
you want your little guns too bad.

819
01:10:53,610 --> 01:10:56,773
So I'm gonna tell you where
to bring Melanie and Tracy,

820
01:10:56,847 --> 01:10:59,042
and we will trade
my family for your guns.

821
01:10:59,116 --> 01:11:01,243
Well, there's always room
for negotiation, Jack.

822
01:11:01,318 --> 01:11:04,879
- I'm listening.
- Port Authority dock, south end.

823
01:11:04,955 --> 01:11:09,551
I'm about, uh, two hours out,
maybe a little more.

824
01:11:09,626 --> 01:11:11,992
- You be there.
- [Phone Beeps]

825
01:11:14,331 --> 01:11:18,734
You better hope that your daddy
knows what he's doin'.

826
01:11:18,802 --> 01:11:22,932
- Ready for this?
- Let's do it.

827
01:11:23,006 --> 01:11:24,974
Okay.

828
01:12:16,893 --> 01:12:19,657
Come on.

829
01:12:46,423 --> 01:12:50,257
- Dad!
- Don't move, honey. It's gonna be okay.

830
01:12:50,327 --> 01:12:52,056
Where are my goods?

831
01:12:55,265 --> 01:12:59,099
- Earl.
- [Machinery Whirring]

832
01:13:07,611 --> 01:13:09,442
I give you a job.

833
01:13:09,513 --> 01:13:13,916
I offer to get
your operator's license back,
and this is how you say thank you?

834
01:13:13,984 --> 01:13:16,179
You let them go, or the whole
load goes in the water.

835
01:13:16,253 --> 01:13:18,687
I can always get more guns.
Can you get a new family?

836
01:13:18,755 --> 01:13:20,279
- Dad!
- Keep still!

837
01:13:20,357 --> 01:13:21,847
- Leave her alone!
- Get your hands off my daughter!

838
01:13:21,925 --> 01:13:24,860
Shut up! Everybody!
Shut up!

839
01:13:24,928 --> 01:13:30,366
- I want my guns.
- I told you not to touch them.

840
01:13:33,270 --> 01:13:36,637
Earl, give Mr. Cutler
some of his goods.

841
01:13:44,347 --> 01:13:46,372
Damn it!

842
01:13:46,449 --> 01:13:49,680
All right, here's the deal.

843
01:13:49,753 --> 01:13:51,914
I'm gonna give you the kid.
Let her go, Vince.

844
01:13:51,988 --> 01:13:54,889
- Let her go!
- [Whimpers]

845
01:13:54,958 --> 01:13:57,222
You tell that monkey to straighten
out that load and put it onto the dock,

846
01:13:57,294 --> 01:13:58,727
and I'll give you
your wife.

847
01:13:58,795 --> 01:14:00,922
[Tires Screeching]

848
01:14:05,502 --> 01:14:07,436
Let's go! Come on!

849
01:14:09,906 --> 01:14:11,931
- Honey, come on. Come on.
- Jack!

850
01:14:25,655 --> 01:14:27,247
Move, move, move!

851
01:14:31,061 --> 01:14:33,655
Up. Up, up, up.

852
01:14:36,866 --> 01:14:39,300
- Ow!
- Move! Come on! Go up!

853
01:14:39,369 --> 01:14:43,863
Stay here. Keep your head down.
I'm gonna go get your mom.

854
01:14:43,940 --> 01:14:46,807
- [Gunfire]
- Keep... goin'!

855
01:14:55,852 --> 01:14:58,377
Aaah! Aah!

856
01:14:58,455 --> 01:15:00,286
[Groans]

857
01:15:22,913 --> 01:15:25,313
- Clear!
- Come on! Let's go!

858
01:15:25,382 --> 01:15:27,282
Grab the other side!

859
01:15:32,022 --> 01:15:35,150
- Come on. Keep movin'. Come on!
- [Melanie] Ow!

860
01:15:35,225 --> 01:15:38,661
- Come on. Move, move, move!
- Let go! Oh!

861
01:15:38,728 --> 01:15:42,220
Move, move, move.
Come on!

862
01:15:55,612 --> 01:15:57,580
Jack!

863
01:15:57,647 --> 01:16:00,775
- [Groans]
- [Cutler Screams]

864
01:16:49,866 --> 01:16:51,595
Jack!

865
01:16:51,668 --> 01:16:54,728
Crews, freeze! F.B.I.!
Put that gun down!

866
01:16:54,804 --> 01:16:57,170
Put it down!

867
01:16:57,240 --> 01:17:00,767
Crews. Come on, Crews.
Let him go.

868
01:17:00,844 --> 01:17:05,281
- It's over.
- [Gasping]

869
01:17:05,348 --> 01:17:08,374
Jack?

870
01:17:13,189 --> 01:17:17,717
- Oh, my God. Are you okay?
- I'm okay.

871
01:17:17,794 --> 01:17:21,958
- Where's Tracy?
- [Ford] She's okay. Kid's okay.

872
01:17:22,032 --> 01:17:23,966
Thank God.

873
01:17:28,171 --> 01:17:30,105
I love you.

874
01:17:35,779 --> 01:17:36,112
[Machinery Whirring]

875
01:17:36,112 --> 01:17:37,704
[Machinery Whirring]

876
01:17:39,149 --> 01:17:41,083
[Chattering]

877
01:17:44,387 --> 01:17:46,321
Okay.

878
01:17:47,991 --> 01:17:52,587
Crews. Thanks for
bringing Sonny's body back.

879
01:17:52,662 --> 01:17:56,792
- I know it'll mean a lot to his family.
- He was a good man.

880
01:17:56,866 --> 01:17:58,891
I was in contact with him
on the truck,

881
01:17:58,968 --> 01:18:02,961
and we would have done all right
by you, even if we hadn't had
our little discussion.

882
01:18:03,039 --> 01:18:06,497
- What discussion?
- Your husband told us
where to find Cutler,

883
01:18:06,576 --> 01:18:09,875
and he brought us the guns.

884
01:18:09,946 --> 01:18:13,643
With the testimony and
the extenuating circumstances,
I think you'll do fine on this.

885
01:18:13,717 --> 01:18:16,948
[Avery] I also think we can find
a way to save your house.

886
01:18:17,020 --> 01:18:20,148
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

887
01:18:20,223 --> 01:18:25,388
Mr. Crews, we were wondering
if you wouldn't mind driving the
truck cab to the impound yard.

888
01:18:25,462 --> 01:18:28,898
Can we, please? Can we?
Can we, Dad?

889
01:18:28,965 --> 01:18:30,899
I don't have a license.

890
01:18:30,967 --> 01:18:35,267
The way I understand it
from Agent Ford,

891
01:18:35,338 --> 01:18:38,535
you do.

892
01:18:42,278 --> 01:18:44,439
Thank you.

893
01:18:47,517 --> 01:18:50,418
(music) He drew first
and I shot faster (music)

894
01:18:50,487 --> 01:18:52,546
Easy, boys.

895
01:18:52,622 --> 01:18:54,749
- Hold this. I'll be back.
- I'm a songwriter.

896
01:18:54,824 --> 01:18:57,793
[Earl] That's what I really do
when I'm not drivin'.

897
01:18:57,861 --> 01:19:01,092
Hey, could you get
my book out of my vest?

898
01:19:01,164 --> 01:19:04,793
All this shootin' and such,
I got an idea for a new song.

899
01:19:04,868 --> 01:19:09,965
[Laughs] Well, you know what.
I bet it'll go platinum.

900
01:19:10,039 --> 01:19:12,200
I hope so.

901
01:19:12,275 --> 01:19:14,402
Thanks for stayin', Earl.

902
01:19:14,477 --> 01:19:18,743
Don't mention it.
I reckon it was worth it.

903
01:19:18,815 --> 01:19:23,275
Hey, Dad, look at this.
Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

904
01:19:23,353 --> 01:19:25,913
- [Tracy] Good doggy.
- Hey, Crews.

905
01:19:25,989 --> 01:19:29,618
You mind lookin' after Tiny
till we get all this sorted out?

906
01:19:29,692 --> 01:19:33,128
You got it.
Good luck.

907
01:19:33,196 --> 01:19:35,164
You take care.

908
01:19:37,267 --> 01:19:39,827
Oh, oh, yeah.

909
01:19:39,903 --> 01:19:42,030
So let's go for a ride.

910
01:19:52,248 --> 01:19:56,617
- You're such a good dog.
- We've got a lot to talk about.

911
01:19:56,686 --> 01:19:58,745
I know.

912
01:20:00,023 --> 01:20:02,821
I'm sorry, Melanie.

913
01:20:04,093 --> 01:20:06,994
I love you, Jack.

914
01:20:07,063 --> 01:20:09,930
I love you too.

915
01:20:15,738 --> 01:20:17,831
Does this mean we can all go
to my game tonight?

916
01:20:17,907 --> 01:20:22,139
As long as you think
we have time to stop and pick up
a pair of high-top tennis shoes.

917
01:20:22,212 --> 01:20:23,941
[Truck Horn Blaring]

918
01:20:24,013 --> 01:20:25,503
- Oh!
- [Grunts]

919
01:20:27,851 --> 01:20:31,048
Welcome to
the Garden State, Crews!

920
01:20:31,120 --> 01:20:33,020
- What was that?
- The hound from hell.

921
01:20:37,227 --> 01:20:39,957
Brace yourselves.
I'm gonna get us out of this.

922
01:20:41,631 --> 01:20:43,963
- What does he want?
- Me.

923
01:20:45,969 --> 01:20:48,494
You wanna play games,
do ya? You wanna play?

